# KTF — Always Apply
Always apply this rule at the start of any coding session.

## Non-Negotiable
- Python 3.12+ only (no older syntax)
- All async code must use `asyncio` (no sync where async is possible)
- Never commit secrets or .env files
- German language for all user-facing strings
- Respect patient data: never log personal information at INFO level or above

## This Project
- Monorepo structure at ~/Dev/krankenfahrt/
- Three Telegram bots: one asyncio process
- SQLite via Tortoise ORM
- DeepSeek for NLU, faster-whisper for voice

## When In Doubt
- Simpler is better. No over-engineering.
- No new dependencies without explicit consideration.
- Telegram handles offline — don't build custom offline logic.
